The Find a Grave site lists her name as Miriam Virginia Hostetter Breed, and says &quot;Last Married to Mr Wm. Zehner Breed of Cleveland Ohio in 1937. he died the following year.&quot;  &nbsp;However, the Baldwin Hills Village article states (in the internal-document-link footnote iii), &quot;Around 1937 she married William Z. Breed, who she met through her interests with show dogs, but he died around 1939. This was followed by a man named Galligan.&quot;

Oddly, the same Baldwin Hills Village article -- just before the footnote iii is displayed says (emphasis added), &quot;as Mr. Smith would be jettisoned shortly thereafter, replaced by <u>at least</u> three more husbands in the years to come.[iii]&quot;  &nbsp;Perhaps the author was unable to confirm how many husbands Miriam had.

So if there was a husband #4 (Galligan), he doesn't even rate a first name -- nor everlasting memory on the gravestone ;)
